    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali9-kilavi">iḵtu uṭaṉpōya talaivipiṉ ceṉṟa cevili iṭaiccurattu mukkōṟpakavaraik 
            kaṇṭu ivvakaippaṭṭārai āṇṭuk kāṇīrōveṉa viṉaviyāṭku, avaraik kaṇṭu aḵtaṟameṉavē 
            karutip pōntēm, nīrum avartiṟattu evvampaṭa vēṇṭāveṉa ētu-kāṭṭi avar teruṭṭiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">This is how the foster mother wo had gone after the eloped heroine sees in the middle of the desert ascetic with three[-pointed] staffs, and they explain to her who asked "have you seen those who acted in this manner there?" by showing the reason: "we have come having seen them, considering that is dharma. You too need not undergo suffering on their account."</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali9">
                <l>eṟittaru katirtāṅki yēntiya kuṭainīḻa</l>
                <l>luṟittāḻnta karakamu muraicāṉṟa mukkōlu</l>
                <l>neṟippaṭac cuvalacaii vēṟōrā neñcattuk</l>
                <l>kuṟippēval ceyaṉmālaik koḷainaṭai yantaṇīr</l>
                <l>vevviṭaic celaṉmālai yoḻukkattī rivviṭai</l>
                <l>yeṉmaka ḷoruttiyum piṟaṇmaka ṉoruvaṉun</l>
                <l>tammuḷē puṇarnta tāmaṟi puṇarcciya</l>
                <l>raṉṉā riruvaraik kāṇirō peruma</l>
                <l>kāṇē mallēṅ kaṇṭaṉaṅ kaṭattiṭai</l>
                <l>yāṇeḻi laṇṇalō ṭaruñcura muṉṉiya</l>
                <l>māṇiḻai maṭavara ṟāyirnīr pōṟir;</l>
                <l rend="space">palavuṟu naṟuñcāntam paṭuppavark kallatai</l>
                <l>malaiyuḷē piṟappiṉu malaikkavaitā meṉceyyu</l>
                <l>niṉaiyuṅkā ṉummaka ṇumakkumāṅ kaṉaiyaḷē;</l>
                <l rend="space">cīrkeḻu veṇmutta maṇipavark kallatai</l>
                <l>nīruḷē piṟappiṉu nīrkkavaitā meṉceyyun</l>
                <l>tēruṅkā ṉummaka ṇumakkumāṅ kaṉaiyaḷē;</l>
                <l rend="space">ēḻpuṇa riṉṉicai muralpavark kallatai</l>
                <l>yāḻuḷē piṟappiṉum yāḻkkavaitā meṉceyyuñ</l>
                <l>cūḻuṅkā ṉummaka ṇumakkumāṅ kaṉaiyaḷē;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>iṟanta kaṟpiṉāṭ kevvam paṭaraṉmiṉ</l>
                <l>ciṟantāṉai vaḻipaṭīic ceṉṟaṉa</l>
                <l>ḷaṟantalai piriyā vāṟumaṟ ṟatuvē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>“Oh brahmins with a gait that holds [your] nature of doing the command intended</l>
                <l>by the heart that does not agree to another, having orderly tied to [your] shoulder</l>
                <l>the pitcher that hangs from the net and the trident worthy to by spoken about,</l>
                <l>enduring the attacking rays in the shade of a raised parasol,</l>
                <l>you with a conduct the nature of which is going on the hot way,</l>
                <l>one girl, my daughter, and one boy, the son of another,</l>
                <l>in a union known to them, that was made in their hearts,</l>
                <l>did you see two people like these, oh great one?”</l>
                <l>“It is not that we did not see [them], we saw [them] on the forest road,</l>
                <l>oh mother of a girls with glorious jewels</l>
                <l>who approached the difficult desert together with a majesty of manly grace,</l>
                <l rend="indent2">you may be like [her].”</l>
                <l>Except for those who produce fragrant sandal that has many,</l>
                <l>although they are born in the mountains, what will they do for the mountain?</l>
                <l>When you think of it, your daughter is like that for you.</l>
                <l>Except for those who adorn themselves with excellent white pearls</l>
                <l>although they are born in the water, what will they do for the water?</l>
                <l>When you examine it, your daughter is like that for you.</l>
                <l>Except for those who make the sweet sounds joined in seven,</l>
                <l>although born in the lute, what will they do for the lute?</l>
                <l>When you consider, your daughter is like that for you.</l>
                <l>That is to say,</l>
                <l>Don’t think about the trouble of her with a fidelity that has gone beyond [your care].</l>
                <l>Worshipping you who is excellent she has gone.</l>
                <l>That too is a path not divided from Dharma.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
